"and drought (DLDD). Parties should be as comprehensive as possible in "
"describing the action plan or programme, identifying the status of the "
"action, any successes achieved and the challenges that are being "
"addressed in its implementation. Parties should also specify whether the "
"plan was developed using a participatory process and, if so, whether "
"women, youth, indigenous people and local communities and their "
"representatives were involved in planning and decision-making."
